headline.main: ITALY GETS 'SHOCKING' NEWS; Loss of Mogadiscio Announced -- More Blows Expected

lead_paragraph: ROME, Feb. 28 -- The shocking news that Mogadiscio, capital of Italian Somaliland, had been evacuated was broken to the Italian people today by the war bulletin, which said that a fierce struggle continued north of the city. After Bengazi this is the hardest blow that the Italian Empire and the Italian pride have received in the war.
